---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy • Fin Sanctuary"
  description="Read the Fin Sanctuary privacy policy covering contact forms, newsletter signup, cookies, analytics, advertising, and external links."
>
  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-primary/10 bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(1,133,174,0.08),rgba(243,239,238,0.55))] dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(13,175,188,0.14),rgba(2,6,23,0.95))]">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10 md:py-12">
        <div class="text-[0.72rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-primary/75">Privacy Policy</div>
        <h1 class="mt-5 font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">How Fin Sanctuary handles visitor information.</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200">
          This policy explains what information may be collected when you use Fin Sanctuary, how that information is used, and what third-party services may interact with the site.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10">
      <article class="rounded-[2rem] border border-primary/10 bg-white px-7 py-8 shadow-[0_24px_80px_-55px_rgba(1,133,174,0.42)] dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-slate-900 md:px-9">
        <div class="space-y-7 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Information You Provide</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">If you submit a contact form, custom print request, support request, or newsletter signup, Fin Sanctuary may receive the information you choose to provide, including your name, email address, and message content.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Basic Site and Device Data</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Like most websites, Fin Sanctuary may collect basic browser and device information such as IP address, browser type, referral source, pages visited, and general usage patterns. This information is used to understand traffic, improve site content, and monitor site performance.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Cookies, Analytics, and Advertising</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Fin Sanctuary may use cookies or similar technologies for analytics, site functionality, and advertising. Google AdSense and other third-party services may use cookies to deliver and measure ads. Analytics or advertising providers may collect data according to their own privacy policies.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Newsletter and Email Communication</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">If you subscribe to a newsletter or contact the site by email, your email address may be used to respond to your message, send newsletter updates, or provide site-related communications that you requested. Fin Sanctuary does not intend to sell visitor email lists.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">The site may link to third-party services such as YouTube, external shops, affiliate programs, and social or analytics tools. Those services operate under their own policies and Fin Sanctuary is not responsible for their separate data practices.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">How Information Is Used</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Information may be used to answer questions, improve guides and site structure, support product and support requests, send newsletter updates, review site traffic trends, and keep advertising and affiliate systems functioning appropriately.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Policy Updates</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">This policy may be updated as the site adds newsletter tooling, storefront integrations, analytics changes, or additional advertising and media features.</p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
